													"value": "An enterprise network is a group of connected computers built to serve the needs of a large business. Enterprise networks may involve thousands of devices that need to connect to each other and the Internet. Unlike the Internet, however, enterprise networks are not open to the public, but are limited to specific users, devices, and facilities.",
